            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="accent-bar"></div>

        <div class="page-title">THE TWO BOOKS FRAMEWORK</div>

        <!-- Philosophy -->
        <div class="philosophy">
            True global macro is directional, not directionally constrained. <strong>Soros didn't break the Bank of England by being bullish on the pound.</strong> We are directional macro, not relative value. We have views. In a world where prices go up most of the time, our bias is towards owning. The framework accommodates wherever the thesis takes us: long or short.
        </div>

        <!-- Two Books -->
        <div class="books-grid">
            <div class="book-box">
                <div class="book-header">
                    CORE BOOK
                    <span>50-100% of Capital • Thesis-Driven</span>
                </div>
                <div class="book-content">
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Driver:</strong> Macro/fundamental thesis across three engines</li>
                        <li><strong>Direction:</strong> Long or short based on thesis</li>
                        <li><strong>Position sizing:</strong> Up to 20% per position</li>
                        <li><strong>Scoring:</strong> 24-point system (Technical + Fundamental + Microstructure)</li>
                        <li><strong>Stops:</strong> Dual framework (Thesis + Price)</li>
                        <li><strong>Horizon:</strong> 3-6 month catalyst expectation</li>
                        <li><strong>Cash:</strong> 30-100% valid when no setups qualify</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="book-box technical">
                <div class="book-header">
                    TECHNICAL OVERLAY
                    <span>0-50% of Capital • Price-Driven</span>
                </div>
                <div class="book-content">
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Driver:</strong> Pure price structure (trend + momentum + RS)</li>
                        <li><strong>Direction:</strong> Long or short based on trend</li>
                        <li><strong>Position sizing:</strong> Up to 10% longs, 5% shorts</li>
                        <li><strong>Scoring:</strong> 12-point system (Trend + Momentum + Relative Strength)</li>
                        <li><strong>Stops:</strong> Price only (tighter)</li>
                        <li><strong>Activation:</strong> When Core Book is defensive (MRI > +1.0)</li>
                        <li><strong>Note:</strong> Trends can last years to decades</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

